Biography
Anthony Cressotti is a Maryland film editor. His work includes the animations, “Bandit Versus Stripe,” “Pilot Bluey,” and “Bandit Needs Some Advice.” 
He has an Associate of Arts degree and studies video production and filmmaking in pursuit of his Audio-Video Media Production Associate of Arts degree at Howard Community College.
His experience includes working with the editing software package, Open Shot Video Editor. 
Writing, editing, and producing for his YouTube platform, Anthony has been focused on creating new animation content for his subscribers. 
He lives and creates film content in Elkridge, Maryland.
